When I ran the decompiler after switching from the 2.0 tagged release to the master, the output changed fairly radically.  It's not apparent to me just why that happens.

It seems that DAD was updated to be much more literal.  Compound expressions are broken down and the version attachment to the variables is gone.  It can sometimes affect readability, like how 
in v2.0:
```
                byte[] v4_8 = ((v3_5[v1_19] & 255) | ((v3_5[(v1_19 + 1)] & 255) << 8));
```
now is
```
                    v4 = v3[v1];
                    v4 &= 255;
                    v5 = (v1 + 1);
                    v5 = v3[v5];
                    v5 &= 255;
                    v5 <<= 8;
                    v4 |= v5;
```

Any thoughts?

